Two block isn't quite wide enough for a pillow

00:04:00.249 --> 00:04:04.409
so we need to take six squares and cut them
in half to add a little width to each side

00:04:04.409 --> 00:04:11.409
of the pillow. Take the half blocks and sew
them into two rows to match your pattern.

00:04:13.089 --> 00:04:18.019
Add one two to the top and bottom of your
pinwheel blocks.

00:04:18.019 --> 00:04:22.270
To make the pillowcase long enough we will
add a column of squares to the end. This will

00:04:22.270 --> 00:04:28.740
be four blocks tall with a half block on each
end. Sew the squares together. Taking the

00:04:28.740 --> 00:04:35.740
long column take the edge that will be end
of the pillowcase and turn on edge under .5

00:04:37.900 --> 00:04:41.750
inch. Sew onto the end of your pinwheel blocks.

00:04:41.750 --> 00:04:47.819
Out of you solid back you will need to cut
a rectangle that is 21 by 28 inches. Turn

00:04:47.819 --> 00:04:53.169
under the end of the pillowcase .5 inches
and sew using a straight stitch.

00:04:53.169 --> 00:04:57.939
With right sides together, Sew the solid back
to the pillowcase front using a .5 inch seam

00:04:57.939 --> 00:05:04.939
allowance. Trim your threads!

